 Note: The new theory is inherently flawed. Why? Because in order to be new, it is necessary to destroy existing assumptions and the like, rather than merely redraw existing ones, but on the other hand, in order to be expressed in the spirit of the times, it is inevitably impossible to move away from existing conceptual structures.
 
 Well, after the second Pomodoro, that is, after 50 minutes of reading this book, I have come to realize that I am interested in Freud's story of the unconscious and repression, but I don't seem to be very interested in the classification of personality structures or the symbolic language of dreams. Why is that, perhaps, because it is "not disprovable. This is not science, just a description of a worldview. The preconceived notion that no matter how widely loved and used the Cthulhu Mythos system is in various works, it does not mean that the Cthulhu Mythos is true. Is this preconception correct? Is it not a fallacy? This "Thinking about the Question" is strictly an assignment for tomorrow, Day 4, but I'll make a note of it so I don't forget.
 
 Note: Q: Is the classification of dream symbolic language and personality structure a science?
 
